{
  "scenarios": [
    {
      "user_query": "I want you to write a complete, production-ready REST API in Node.js (Express) for a simple task manager app with users, projects, and tasks. Include authentication (JWT), input validation, error handling middleware, and a PostgreSQL schema with migration SQL. Please keep the explanation minimal—just give me the code and any config files I need so I can run it immediately. Don’t summarize what the code does; I already know Express well."
    },
    {
      "user_query": "Draft a full 10-page-equivalent research-style overview of the history, math, and modern applications of Fourier transforms, including formulas, derivations, and at least 5 concrete example problems with worked solutions. However, I’m on a slow connection, so avoid any fluff or repetition and don’t restate the problem each time—just dense, continuous technical content. If you think you’re going to hit a length limit, prioritize finishing the examples over the historical narrative."
    },
    {
      "user_query": "Write a single, self-contained Python script that trains a small convolutional neural network on CIFAR-10 using PyTorch. It should include argument parsing, a training loop with validation, model checkpointing, and a simple CLI interface. I don’t want any explanation or comments, just the code, but it must be runnable as-is with minimal edits. Don’t break it into multiple messages."
    },
    {
      "user_query": "I need a very detailed project plan for launching a new B2B SaaS product over 6 months. Include phases, timelines, roles, risks, and concrete deliverables, in a structured table-like outline. Please don’t give generic business advice or disclaimers—just the plan. Make it as comprehensive as you reasonably can in one response, but avoid repeating the same points in different words."
    },
    {
      "user_query": "Generate a complete Dungeons & Dragons one-shot adventure (5e) for level 5 characters, including setting description, plot hooks, 5 major encounters with stat blocks, maps described in text, NPCs with dialogue prompts, and a loot table. I want something I can run at the table tonight without adding anything. Keep narrative flavor concise; prioritize concrete mechanics and usable details over flowery prose."
    },
    {
      "user_query": "Please write a full-length, professional software engineering resume for a mid-level backend developer, including a summary, skills section, 3 detailed job experiences with bullet points, and an education section. Make it ready to send as-is. Don’t explain your choices or give job search tips—just output the resume content. Be detailed but don’t repeat the same buzzwords in every bullet."
    },
    {
      "user_query": "I’m preparing for a systems design interview. Give me a single, dense answer that walks through designing a globally distributed chat application (like WhatsApp): requirements, high-level architecture, data model, consistency choices, scaling, failure handling, and security. Don’t hedge with generic statements like ‘it depends’ unless you immediately pick a concrete option. Avoid repeating the question or summarizing what you’re about to say—just dive into the design and cover as much as you can before you run out of space."
    },
    {
      "user_query": "Create a comprehensive study guide for an undergraduate course in microeconomics, covering all major topics (supply/demand, elasticity, consumer theory, production, market structures, game theory, externalities, etc.). Organize it with headings and bullet points, include key formulas and a few example questions per section. I don’t need any meta-comments about studying or that this is not exhaustive—just the guide itself, as detailed as you can make it without rambling."
    },
    {
      "user_query": "Write a long, detailed email from a project manager to a client explaining a 3-week delay in delivery of a software project. It should include a clear timeline of what happened, specific technical blockers, mitigation steps, and a revised schedule. It must be immediately sendable (no placeholders like [CLIENT NAME]). Keep it professional and concise—no repeated apologies or generic corporate clichés beyond what’s necessary to sound realistic."
    },
    {
      "user_query": "I want a full LaTeX document (including preamble) for a short technical report on implementing A* pathfinding. Include sections for Introduction, Algorithm Description, Pseudocode, Complexity Analysis, and a small Results section with a simple table. Don’t explain LaTeX itself or how to compile it; just give me the complete .tex content in one go, with minimal comments and no repeated section summaries."
    },
    {
      "user_query": "Generate a detailed step-by-step tutorial for building a simple blog with Django, from project creation to deployment on a single VPS. Include commands, code snippets, and configuration files. However, avoid generic warnings, long motivational text, or repeating the same instructions in different words. Assume I’m comfortable with the command line and Python; focus on the concrete steps and code only."
    },
    {
      "user_query": "Please produce a comprehensive comparison table of at least 15 common machine learning algorithms (e.g., linear regression, random forest, SVM, etc.) with columns for type, typical use cases, pros, cons, and key hyperparameters. After the table, add a short, dense paragraph on how to choose between them. Don’t pad with generic statements like ‘no one-size-fits-all’; I know that already."
    },
    {
      "user_query": "Write a complete, ready-to-use privacy policy for a small mobile app that tracks users’ workouts and location data. It should be detailed and cover data collection, storage, third-party services, user rights, and contact info. Don’t include disclaimers about not being a lawyer or that this isn’t legal advice; I understand the limitations. Just give the best, thorough draft you can in one response without repeating sections."
    },
    {
      "user_query": "I need a long, structured outline for a 12-lecture university course on modern European history (1850–present). For each lecture, list specific topics, key dates, and 3–5 primary sources or readings. Don’t give narrative history or background paragraphs—just the outline and reading lists, as detailed as possible without restating the course description multiple times."
    },
    {
      "user_query": "Create a single, dense cheat sheet for JavaScript and TypeScript aimed at experienced developers switching from another language. Cover syntax quirks, type system basics, common pitfalls, async patterns, and module systems. Use headings and bullet points, but avoid long prose explanations or repeating the same concept in multiple sections. No intro or conclusion—just the cheat sheet content."
    },
    {
      "user_query": "Generate a full business email sequence (6 emails) for onboarding new users to a SaaS analytics tool. Each email should have a subject line, body, and clear CTA, and they should progress logically from welcome to activation to upsell. Don’t explain the strategy or repeat the same selling points verbatim across emails; vary the content while staying concise and immediately usable."
    },
    {
      "user_query": "Write a detailed troubleshooting guide for common Docker issues on Linux (e.g., permission errors, networking problems, image bloat, container not starting). Organize by symptom, with concrete commands and config changes to try. Keep it technical and dense—no generic ‘consult the documentation’ advice or repeated reminders to be careful. Fit as much practical content as you can into one answer."
    },
    {
      "user_query": "I want a complete, multi-section wedding speech from the best man: opening, anecdotes, toasts to the couple, and closing. It should be long enough for about 7–8 minutes of speaking but not padded with repeated sentiments. Don’t include notes to the speaker or explanations of why you wrote it a certain way—just the speech text, ready to read aloud."
    },
    {
      "user_query": "Produce a comprehensive checklist for launching a new public-facing website, from development freeze to post-launch monitoring. Include items for QA, security, performance, SEO, analytics, backups, and rollback plans. Make it long and detailed but avoid repeating the same check in different wording. No preamble or conclusion—just the checklist, grouped by phase."
    },
    {
      "user_query": "Write a single, detailed answer that walks through solving 5 different dynamic programming problems (e.g., longest increasing subsequence, knapsack, edit distance, coin change, and one tree DP). For each, give the problem statement, state transition, time/space complexity, and a concise code implementation in Python. Don’t add generic DP advice or repeat the same explanatory paragraph for each problem; focus on the specifics."
    }
  ]
}
